race.comment: MADE IN ITALY (6) was beaten for speed here on debut but impressed finding the line strongly beaten 1L over 1400m. Open to sharp improvement and drawn better can get off the mark. LUNA BAY (4) sat behind the leader beaten 1.5L in the same contest on debut as a $4.4 favourite. Will jump from an inside barrier and fitter is feared. BELLA WAHINE (2) just missed at Newcastle on debut and needed the first-up run in town. Maps well and up in trip quick improvement is likely. BONDI BLOSSOM (9) led and placed at Hawkesbury first-up over 1300m. Has to run out the extra 200m but maps well and will get every chance. LET'S BE HONEST (8) draws out but wasn't beaten far here on debut and it was a tough effort. She will appreciate the longer trip.
